        "content": "{\n  \"resolution_strategies\": [\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS1_make_rejection_status_sticky_in_direct_questions\",\n      \"change_operations\": [\n        {\n          \"operation\": \"modify_write\",\n          \"parameters\": {\n            \"target_activity_label\": \"direct questions\",\n            \"new_statement\": \"assessment_status = if data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\" then \\\"rejected\\\" else <direct_questions_assessment_result>\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"full\",\n          \"reason\": \"If 'conduct interview and questionnaire' sets assessment_status to rejected, 'direct questions' will preserve the rejected value instead of overwriting it. Therefore, the subsequent XOR condition 'data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\"' will be true and the process will execute 'inform of rejection' followed directly by 'terminate'. Rejections produced by 'direct questions' are also still handled by the existing rejected branch.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"high\",\n          \"reason\": \"The strategy preserves the existing activities, resources, ordering, parallel structure, timeout behavior, and both assessment_status writes required by the context requirements. It does not affect R1, R2, R3, R4, or R7.\"\n        },\n        \"change_cost\": {\n          \"value\": \"very_low\",\n          \"reason\": \"Only one localized data-write modification is required in the activity immediately before the compliance-relevant XOR decision.\"\n        },\n        \"structural_quality_impact\": {\n          \"value\": \"none\",\n          \"reason\": \"The process control-flow structure is unchanged. No new branches, loops, or activities are introduced.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"The change is located in the assessment part of the process, after consent handling and before the rejection or venepuncture decision.\"\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS2_prevent_conduct_interview_from_setting_rejected\",\n      \"change_operations\": [\n        {\n          \"operation\": \"modify_write\",\n          \"parameters\": {\n            \"target_activity_label\": \"conduct interview and questionnaire\",\n            \"new_statement\": \"assessment_status = \\\"requires_direct_questions\\\"\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"full\",\n          \"reason\": \"The violation arises because 'conduct interview and questionnaire' can set assessment_status to rejected before 'direct questions' potentially overwrites it. By ensuring that 'conduct interview and questionnaire' no longer writes the rejected value, the only activity that can set assessment_status to rejected is 'direct questions', which is immediately followed by the XOR branch that informs the donor of rejection and then terminates.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"The listed context requirements remain structurally satisfied: the activity still writes assessment_status, and resources and ordering are unchanged. However, this strategy changes the semantic role of 'conduct interview and questionnaire' by removing its ability to directly reject, which may be less desirable from a business perspective.\"\n        },\n        \"change_cost\": {\n          \"value\": \"very_low\",\n          \"reason\": \"Only a single write statement is modified.\"\n        },\n        \"structural_quality_impact\": {\n          \"value\": \"none\",\n          \"reason\": \"No control-flow structure is changed. The repair is purely data-oriented.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"The modification is made in the assessment subprocess before the rejection decision.\"\n        }\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS3_add_prior_rejection_flag_to_branch_condition\",\n      \"change_operations\": [\n        {\n          \"operation\": \"add_write\",\n          \"parameters\": {\n            \"target_activity_label\": \"conduct interview and questionnaire\",\n            \"added_statement\": \"prior_rejection = (data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\")\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"operation\": \"modify_condition\",\n          \"parameters\": {\n            \"target_activity_label\": \"inform of rejection\",\n            \"new_condition\": \"data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\" or data.prior_rejection\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"operation\": \"modify_condition\",\n          \"parameters\": {\n            \"target_activity_label\": \"prepare for venepuncture\",\n            \"new_condition\": \"not (data.assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\" or data.prior_rejection)\"\n          }\n        }\n      ],\n      \"evaluation\": {\n        \"compliance_degree\": {\n          \"value\": \"full\",\n          \"reason\": \"The added flag records whether 'conduct interview and questionnaire' produced a rejected assessment. Even if 'direct questions' later overwrites assessment_status, the rejection branch will still be selected because the branch condition also checks prior_rejection. The existing direct succession from 'inform of rejection' to 'terminate' remains unchanged.\"\n        },\n        \"resolution_context_consistency\": {\n          \"value\": \"high\",\n          \"reason\": \"All existing context requirements are preserved. The activities, resources, parallel blocks, timeout behavior, and assessment_status writes remain in place.\"\n        },\n        \"change_cost\": {\n          \"value\": \"medium\",\n          \"reason\": \"This strategy requires three changes: one additional write and two branch-condition modifications.\"\n        },\n        \"structural_quality_impact\": {\n          \"value\": \"low\",\n          \"reason\": \"The control-flow structure remains unchanged, but the decision logic becomes more complex because it introduces and relies on an additional data flag.\"\n        },\n        \"change_location\": {\n          \"value\": \"middle\",\n          \"reason\": \"All modifications are localized around the assessment-status evaluation and rejection decision.\"\n        }\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"best_resolution_strategy_id\": \"RS1_make_rejection_status_sticky_in_direct_questions\",\n  \"best_resolution_reason\": \"RS1 is the preferred strategy because it fully restores compliance with a single localized data-write change, preserves all listed resolution context requirements, and does not alter the process control-flow structure. It also maintains the possibility that either assessment activity can contribute to rejection while ensuring that once a rejection has been produced, it cannot be overwritten before the rejection-handling branch.\",\n  \"alternative_suggestion\": {\n    \"reason\": \"A structurally explicit repair would require inserting a new XOR decision immediately after 'conduct interview and questionnaire' with a rejected branch containing both 'inform of rejection' and 'terminate', and a non-rejected branch continuing to 'direct questions'. The provided operations do not directly support inserting a complete XOR block with a multi-activity branch at that exact point without risking an unconditional terminate or an incomplete branch structure.\",\n    \"conceptual_solution\": \"After 'conduct interview and questionnaire', add an explicit decision: if assessment_status == \\\"rejected\\\", execute 'inform of rejection' followed directly by 'terminate'; otherwise continue to 'direct questions' and the existing assessment-status decision.\",\n    \"expected_compliance_impact\": \"This would fully satisfy the rejection-handling requirement and make the compliance logic more explicit, but it is not directly expressible with the available change operations.\"\n  }\n}",
